data.text:
Plot[]

Peggy and George almost catch Kathy and Alex in a passionate embrace. Grant has a drunken brotherly chat with Phil and explains his hopes for another baby. Tiffany lies awake in bed - feeling unloved and like a 'baby machine'. Bianca and Tiffany have a girlie dress-choosing session and Grant over reacts thinking Tiffany's only interested in impressing other men. He demands she starts acting like his wife and not like a slut. The bailiffs visit Pat and demand cash - Frank comes to her rescue and offers to settle the debt. Steven has a very low-key birthday party. The Vic's party gets underway with songs and party-turns format all the regulars. Grant refuses to tolerate any more of Tiffany's flirting and threatens her.

Notes[]

This episode was broadcast on a Friday at 7.40pm as an extra episode for Boxing Day.
